Chat Encoder is a Shortcut for Conversation and Chat Shortcuts request. It’s based von S-GPT Encoder by Federico Viticci. Moritz Zimmer added several optimizations and expansions, e.g. Internationalization.
Version History
16.08.2025, v1.5 - Added more essential JSON encodings - Added comment with version history
Older optimizations not versioned.
To choose a translation, please enter the ISO 639 Set 1 language code here. Default is "en" for English.
This is a helper shortcut for S-GPT that needs to be downloaded and installed separately. Without this shortcut, S-GPT won't work.

Version: 1.0.2 Build date: 13/4/2023
Version: 1.0.1 Build date: 7/4/2023

{ "en": { "lang-name": "English", "lang-code": "en", "ui-yes": "Yes", "ui-no": "No", "ui-playlist-name": "I will create a playlist for you. Enter a name for your new playlist:", "ui-playlist-added": "Playlist created. Songs added to the playlist:", "ui-open-link-question": "Open links from ChatGPT's response? The shortcut will continue to run.", "prompt-summarize" : "Please provide a summary of the following text:" }, "de": { "lang-name": "Deutsch", "lang-code": "de", "ui-yes": "Ja", "ui-no": "Nein", "ui-playlist-name": "Ich werde eine Playlist kreieren. Gib einen Namen an:", "ui-playlist-added": "Playlist erstellt. Anzahl Songs:", "ui-open-link-question": "Links in der Antwort öffnen? Der Kurzbefehl wird fortgesetzt.", "prompt-summarize" : "Bitte fasse den folgenden Text zuammen:" } }
This means we're triggering one the special modes.
Add a time delay to allow the shortcut to catch up
Set an empty numeric variable so that we can count how many songs we're adding to the playlist.
Start iterating on the lines of text returned by ChatGPT and split them at the custom separator.
Use iTunes Store search in lieu of a native Apple Music search action.
Check if the output contains links and offer to open them
Check for URLs using Gruber's pattern: https://gist.github.com/gruber/8891611
Word count is okay, you can continue.

Below, I'm going to give you a list of my tasks and calendar events for the next 5 days.
Tasks:
￼
Events:
￼
I need you to act like my assistant and tell me which days are overbooked, and whether I should do something about it. Be concise.
Today is ￼.

￼
These songs must be real and not a product of your imagination. They must be available on either Spotify or Apple Music; YouTube alone is not enough.
The playlist should be a list of text with each line in this format:
Artist Name %%SEPARATOR%% Song Name
That's the name of the artist for the song, followed by a space, followed by %%SEPARATOR%%, followed by a space, followed by the name of the song. Use newline characters to separate each line.
Your response should only be the list of text with no additional sentences.
